    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/349.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that little of
                    importance in the political situation has occurred since my arrival here and
                    that everything continues to center around the coming presidential elections,
                    notwithstanding their comparative remoteness. President Arosemena is apparently
                    most anxious to secure his reelection, and for the purpose of satisfying (as his
                    partisans claim) the constitutional requirement is generally expected to avail
                    himself early next month of the leave of absence granted to him by the Supreme
                    Court.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. Percival Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
